<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Remark.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">The Chinese specimens were identified as this species by the yellowish-brown pronotum with a black stripe and the apical process of aedeagus triangular, which is acute and strongly curved downwards. This species was previously only known from Vietnam.</paragraph>
